Description: Asthma is a serious chronic medical condition which has a big impact on those who suffer from it.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Asthma is a serious chronic medical condition which has a big impact on those who suffer from it. The burden of asthma impacts those diagnosed and their families in many ways, including medical care, effects on school and work, and lower quality of life reported on surveys. Some of the facts regarding asthma are: Asthma is the most common chronic disease among children and a leading cause of missed school days and work days for parents. There are 34 million Americans diagnosed with asthma and approximately one third of them are under the age of 18. An estimated 300 million people worldwide suffer from asthma symptoms. It is estimated that the number of people with asthma will grow by more than 100 million by 2025. The good news is asthma can be managed and controlled! With proper medications, avoidance of triggers and monitoring of asthma symptoms, people with asthma can lead healthy, normal lives. This website is dedicated to education, tracking of asthma symptoms and management of asthma through a multidisciplinary team approach. The most important person in the asthma team is you! Our goal is to empower you with the skills and tools needed to help you control your asthma symptoms along with working together with your primary care provider and the asthma team to help you manage your asthma.

Description: Dialoguers builds technology tools to digitally augment the performance of mental health therapists.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Dialoguers is building the first generation of technology tools to digitally augment the performance of mental health therapists. We create simple feedback loops that encourage consistent and unbiased treatment of the patient in the therapy room. While we expect consistency from our professionals research has shown that there are 3 problems; Firstly professionals judgement is strongly influenced by irrelevant factors such as current mood, the time since their last meal, the last person they met and the weather are some examples of unconscious bias. Secondly long experience on a job always increases people's confidence in their own judgement, however confidence is no guarantee of the accuracy or consistency of those judgments. Lastly behavioural psychology has shown that even simple algorithms outperform humans. We're changing that by providing timely and pertinent feedback which will improve results for both patients and therapists.

Description: The lessons we learn both in the classroom and about ourselves are arguably the greatest value of a graduate education
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: The lessons we learn both in the classroom and about ourselves are arguably the greatest value of a graduate education, but they aren’t effective if we don’t take the time to process and internalize them. Yet, when can you consciously reflect upon, process, and reshape your goals during graduate school? How can you make sure the lessons you learn throughout the year aren’t shuffled aside in the hurry to move on to the next step? These are the questions we asked ourselves as first year Wharton MBA students. We had met at the beginning of school and bonded over our mutual love for teaching yoga. Months later, we discussed how much (or maybe just how little) had changed for us during school—whether our goals had shifted, what disappointments we had encountered, what personal discoveries we had made along the way. We felt it was important to set aside time at the end of the year to actively contemplate these things, and we wanted to share this experience with others. And thus the idea for the LeadUp was born!

Description: We opened our doors at the The Bucket BBQ in February of 2013.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: We opened our doors at the The Bucket BBQ in February of 2013. We purchased the LLC (East End Creamery LLC) which included the building and property. We modeled the BBQ after a very successful concept in Orlando Florida called 4 Rivers Smokehouse.   The BBQ restaurants in Upstate NY are usually full service, while we offer cafeteria style with a comfortable and rustic atmosphere. We pulled capital together from different sources for the remodel, kitchen equipment and start-up costs.  We are seeking to combine  this debt and raise the needed capital for promoting the restaurant, operational expenses, the addition of a bar in the loft area and a second location (The Little Bucket BBQ) in a new downtown building project called the Plaza of the Arts. This location will be in combination with a self-serve yogurt shop and a cafe serving Starbucks coffee and tea (We will be using our restaurant name ""Rosalie's"" that has been in existence for eighteen years in Skaneateles, NY).  We will be smoking and cooking everything at the main restaurant to reduce build-out costs of a full kitchen and there will be limited labor in just serving our food at this location.  The city of Auburn has been promoting a Musical Theater Festival with the construction of multiple theaters, a Hilton Garden Inn and new restaurants/bars in the downtown area. They call it ""Broadway in the Fingerlakes"", in which they have  spent millions of dollars to attract tourism to the area by developing this theater district for the future revitalization of the city.  The city is becoming a destination with the musical theater festival and the promotion of it being ""History's Hometown"" as the birthplace of talking movies, The William Seward Home , The Harriet Tubman House and other historical attractions.  We are seeking $375,000 to combine the present start-up debt, operational expenses, expansion and the new location.  Please check out our websites: www.thebucketbbq.com  & www.rosaliescucina.com
